      "description": "`webhook/worker/runtime.rs` uses `.expect()` when spawning delivery workers; under resource pressure this can abort the whole CLI. Return `Result` (or equivalent) and degrade to synchronous delivery or disable webhooks for the run with a clear operator-visible warning. Outcome: webhook subsystem does not crash the process on thread spawn failure.\n\nValidation: `WebhookDispatcher::new` in `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime.rs` panics on `startup_sender.send`, `thread::Builder::spawn`, startup `recv_timeout`, and `dispatcher_for_config` uses `.expect(\"dispatcher initialized\")` on the cached dispatcher.",
